"I didn't mean to.. " 
"art should comfort the disturbed and disturb the comfortable". "if it's good then I owe you, if it's not, you owe me some overtime, is that a deal?"
"Yes! it's a deal!" laura thought she would get fired right there and then. but she didn't. or maybe she still could.. now that she has something on her...  the feeling of impending doom was looming over her.  she thinks to herslef that she never should have allowed herself to think of her novel at work, it's the first job she's found in 3 years, but the novel has been her work for so long, she did it without even thinking. maybe she should have taken that cleaning job, at least there would be no computer and no distractions... who knows if it's still available, if she gets fired her mom will finally kick her out of the house. She already wants to do it bc she thinks her boyfriend is looking at her funny. And maybe he is.. but he's the one that should be going not her. "fuck. I need this job. I need this job to get a place of my own. I have to fix this. "

bea enters her office and looks at all her work layed out on the meeting table and she's ok now, her mind is racing with ideas. she loves her job and she loves people. the 20 minutes before the meeting pass in a second. She grabs a cutter and opens a box of baci, eats one of the chocolates and puts 2 in her pocket, grabs her folder and heads toward the elevator 

[?] to talk to Christopher. He was the one that voted no to her name on the building and also the one that always supported all her pitches. He's fairly old and tired but his bite is still that of a shark.??? tmi, how would E know this??? 

